<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1269,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[151,458,1269,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2007) Novos taxons e notas sobre Acanthoderini (Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) com articulo III dos palpos labiais truncado. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 47 (16), 187 - 190." type="journal article" year="2007">Martins &amp; Galileo (2007)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="Tavakilian &amp; Neouze, 2007" authorityName="Tavakilian &amp; Neouze" authorityYear="2007" box="[584,1206,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[584,862,1269,1293]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Punctozotroctes hovorei</emphasis>
Tavakilian &amp; Néouze, 2007
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1287,1355,1269,1294]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1378,1432,1270,1294]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Pará</collectingRegion>
, Cachimbo) based on a single male (Fig. 5). A recent examination of this specimen reveals that it is a male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins, Galileo" authorityName="Martins, Galileo" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. inhamum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[263,784,1341,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" refString="Martins, U. R., Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Limeira-de-Oliveira, F. (2009) Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Estado do Maranhao, Brasil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 49 (19), 229 - 247." type="journal article" year="2009">Martins, Galileo &amp; Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[973,1041,1341,1366]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1056,1174,1341,1366]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, Caxias). The 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,1341,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">holotype</typeStatus>
of the later is deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[522,595,1378,1402]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">MZSP</collectionCode>
collection and allows us to be sure about the identity of the specimen mistakenly confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[444,553,1413,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[444,553,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[723,1009,1413,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2007) Novos taxons e notas sobre Acanthoderini (Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) com articulo III dos palpos labiais truncado. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 47 (16), 187 - 190." type="journal article" year="2007">Martins &amp; Galileo (2007)</bibRefCitation>
(translated): “The color pattern that is closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[265,557,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[265,557,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Punctozotroctes inhamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[565,656,1449,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,656,1449,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tavakilian &amp; Neouze, 2007" authorityName="Tavakilian &amp; Neouze" authorityYear="2007" box="[773,1211,1449,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[773,883,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
Tavakilian &amp; Néouze, 2007
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1355,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum">
<emphasis box="[1222,1355,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. inhamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the elytral punctation being much finer and only slightly distinct dorsally from middle to apex; by only a few black elytral bands in 
<taxonomicName box="[414,549,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum">
<emphasis box="[414,549,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. inhamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while they are abundant in 
<taxonomicName box="[892,1004,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[892,1004,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, the prothorax is more deeply constricted at the base in 
<taxonomicName box="[524,634,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[524,634,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName box="[732,865,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum">
<emphasis box="[732,865,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. inhamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” Lastly, 
<taxonomicName box="[976,1086,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[976,1086,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more robust body shape than 
<taxonomicName box="[206,338,1593,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhamum">
<emphasis box="[206,338,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. inhamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1269,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Accordingly, 
<taxonomicName box="[352,462,1629,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Punctozotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[352,462,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">P. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 6) is formally excluded from the Brazilian fauna and remains known only from French Guiana.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
